.TH "arc_emac_rx_stall_check" 9 "arc_emac_rx_stall_check" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
arc_emac_rx_stall_check \- check RX stall
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" arc_emac_rx_stall_check
.BI "(struct net_device *ndev "  ","
.BI "int budget "  ","
.BI "unsigned int work_done "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ndev" 12
Pointer to the net_device structure.
.IP "budget" 12
How many BDs requested to process on 1 call.
.IP "work_done" 12
How many BDs processed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Under certain conditions EMAC stop reception of incoming packets and
continuously increment R_MISS register instead of saving data into
provided buffer. This function detect that condition and restart
EMAC.
